        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 6. Ophiambix macrodonta, new species, holotype (NSMT E-13059) (A–E, G, H) and a paratype (NSMT E-13060) (F), SEM images. A, aboral disc and proximal portion of arm; B, aboral periphery of disc and proximal portion of arm; C, granules (arrow heads) on aboral disc; D, oral disc and proximal portion of arms; E, jaws, an arrow head indicates teeth or oral papillae; F, a jaw from lateral view, arrow heads indicate teeth and oral papillae; G, proximal portion of aboral surface of arm, arrow heads indicate supplementary plates; H, proximal portion of oral surface of arm. Abbreviations: ASh, adoral shield; ASp, arm spine; D, dorsal arm plate; GS, genital slit; RS, radial shield; V, ventral arm plate." ;
